<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1224,2010]" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,316,1397,1421]" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Gyulai, 2018" authorityName="Gyulai" authorityYear="2018" box="[322,508,1397,1421]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanceolata" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[322,508,1397,1421]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">Xestia lanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[514,574,1397,1421]" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[514,574,1397,1421]" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[588,708,1398,1421]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1828,1850]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,266,1787]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,261,1808]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Adults. 1. Xestia lanceolata sp. n., holotype, male, China, Yünnan (PGM); 2. Xestia lanceolata sp. n., paratype, male, China, Yünnan (PGM); 3. Xestia lanceolata sp. n., paratype, male, China, Yünnan (PGM); 4. Xestia diagrapha (Boursin, 1963), male, China, Sichuan (PGM); 5. Xestia diagrapha (Boursin, 1963), male, China, Sichuan (PGM); 6. Brachylomia pygmaea (Draudt, 1950), male, China, Sichuan (PGM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608055/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">Figs 1, 2, 3</figureCitation>
) is a medium sized species, similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Boursin, 1963)" authorityName="Boursin" authorityYear="1963" baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[1120,1436,1397,1421]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diagrapha">
<emphasis box="[1120,1260,1397,1421]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">X. diagrapha</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Boursin, Ch." box="[1275,1428,1398,1421]" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" pagination="9 - 107" refId="ref1394" refString="Boursin, Ch. (1963) Die Noctuinae Arten (Agrotinae vulgo sensu) aus Dr. h. c. H. Hone's China-Ausbeuten. Forschungsberichte des Landes Nordhein-Westfalen, 1170, 9 - 107. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 3 - 663 - 07024 - 5" type="journal article" year="1963">Boursin, 1963</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[158,254,1432,1455]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1828,1850]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,266,1787]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,261,1808]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Adults. 1. Xestia lanceolata sp. n., holotype, male, China, Yünnan (PGM); 2. Xestia lanceolata sp. n., paratype, male, China, Yünnan (PGM); 3. Xestia lanceolata sp. n., paratype, male, China, Yünnan (PGM); 4. Xestia diagrapha (Boursin, 1963), male, China, Sichuan (PGM); 5. Xestia diagrapha (Boursin, 1963), male, China, Sichuan (PGM); 6. Brachylomia pygmaea (Draudt, 1950), male, China, Sichuan (PGM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608055/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">Figs 4-5</figureCitation>
), from which it is best distinguished by the size, some of the external features and the study of the male genitalia. The distinguishing external features are as follows: the new species is significantly larger than 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[1293,1436,1466,1490]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diagrapha">
<emphasis box="[1293,1436,1466,1490]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">X. diagrapha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<quantity box="[158,279,1502,1525]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" unit="mm" value="29.0" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="28.0">28–30 mm</quantity>
, versus 
<quantity box="[369,491,1502,1525]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" unit="mm" value="25.0" valueMax="26.0" valueMin="24.0">24–26 mm</quantity>
); the male antennae bipectinate versus finely ciliate in the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[1139,1282,1501,1525]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diagrapha">
<emphasis box="[1139,1282,1501,1525]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">X. diagrapha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the forewing apex is more elongate; the ground colour of the forewings, including the basal area, is darker and greyish,, versus brownish in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[284,425,1570,1594]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diagrapha">
<emphasis box="[284,425,1570,1594]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">X. diagrapha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the basal area conspicuously whitish. Hindwings of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gyulai" authorityYear="2018" box="[1040,1182,1570,1594]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanceolata">
<emphasis box="[1040,1182,1570,1594]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">X. lanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are also darker, greyish and not light brown; the orbicular stigmata are elongate, larger than in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[970,1115,1605,1629]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diagrapha">
<emphasis box="[970,1115,1605,1629]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">X. diagrapha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and without the fine white encircling.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1224,2010]" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">
Another somewhat similar, but not related species is 
<emphasis box="[760,1000,1674,1698]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">Brachylomia pygmaea</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Draudt, M." box="[1014,1159,1675,1698]" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" pagination="1 - 174" refId="ref1480" refString="Draudt, M. (1950) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Agrotiden-Fauna Chinas aus den Ausbeuten Dr. H. Hone's. (Beitrag zur Fauna Sinica) Mitteilungen der Munchner Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 40 (1), 1 - 174." type="journal article" year="1950">Draudt, 1950</bibRefCitation>
), (
<figureCitation box="[1185,1251,1675,1698]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1828,1850]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,266,1787]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,261,1808]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Adults. 1. Xestia lanceolata sp. n., holotype, male, China, Yünnan (PGM); 2. Xestia lanceolata sp. n., paratype, male, China, Yünnan (PGM); 3. Xestia lanceolata sp. n., paratype, male, China, Yünnan (PGM); 4. Xestia diagrapha (Boursin, 1963), male, China, Sichuan (PGM); 5. Xestia diagrapha (Boursin, 1963), male, China, Sichuan (PGM); 6. Brachylomia pygmaea (Draudt, 1950), male, China, Sichuan (PGM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608055/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gyulai" authorityYear="2018" box="[1270,1412,1674,1698]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanceolata">
<emphasis box="[1270,1412,1674,1698]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">X. lanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is somewhat larger (
<quantity box="[344,463,1710,1733]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" unit="mm" value="29.0" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="28.0">28–30 mm</quantity>
, versus 
<quantity box="[551,669,1710,1733]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" unit="mm" value="26.0" valueMax="27.0" valueMin="25.0">25–27 mm</quantity>
) and differs significantly in the more elongate forewing apex; in being much darker and greyish (not yellowish); in the more elongate orbicular and reniform stigmata; the much darker hindwings and darker undersides of all the wings, with the conspicuous presence of the discal spot in the hindwing, which is not visible in the whitish hindwing of 
<emphasis box="[653,787,1814,1837]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">B. pygmaea.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1224,2010]" lastBlockId="1.[151,1436,151,209]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="446" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">
In the male genitalia, the differences between 
<taxonomicName authority="Gyulai, 2018" authorityName="Gyulai" authorityYear="2018" box="[693,836,1847,1872]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanceolata" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[693,836,1847,1872]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">X. lanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[843,903,1848,1872]" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[843,903,1848,1872]" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[956,1097,1847,1872]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diagrapha">
<emphasis box="[956,1097,1847,1872]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">X. diagrapha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are found in the shape and size of the uncus, harpe, cucullus, aedeagus and in the configuration of the vesica. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gyulai" authorityYear="2018" box="[1003,1147,1882,1906]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanceolata">
<emphasis box="[1003,1147,1882,1906]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">X. lanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1162,1258,1883,1906]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–10" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1898,1920]" captionTargetBox="[242,1336,336,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,330,1877]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7–10. Male genitalia. 7. Xestia lanceolata sp. n., holotype, China, Yünnan, slide no. GYP4934 (PGM); 8. Xestia lanceolata sp. n., paratype, China, Yünnan, slide no. GYP4904 (PGM); 9. Xestia diagrapha (Boursin, 1963), China, Sichuan, slide no. GYP2376 (PGM); 10. Brachylomia pygmaea (Draudt, 1950), China, Sichuan, slide no. GYP4905 (PGM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608057/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">Figs 7, 8</figureCitation>
) differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1963" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diagrapha">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">X. diagrapha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[279,345,1918,1941]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–10" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1898,1920]" captionTargetBox="[242,1336,336,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,330,1877]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7–10. Male genitalia. 7. Xestia lanceolata sp. n., holotype, China, Yünnan, slide no. GYP4934 (PGM); 8. Xestia lanceolata sp. n., paratype, China, Yünnan, slide no. GYP4904 (PGM); 9. Xestia diagrapha (Boursin, 1963), China, Sichuan, slide no. GYP2376 (PGM); 10. Brachylomia pygmaea (Draudt, 1950), China, Sichuan, slide no. GYP4905 (PGM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608057/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) by its strong, lanceolate, apically hooked uncus (it is spatulate and broadly flattened apically in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1963" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diagrapha">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="445">X. diagrapha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); larger, longer and not falciform harpe, and larger cucullus. Additionally, the broadly tubular vesica, recurved dorsad with a robust, elongate, sclerotized bar, deriving from the medio-dorsal section of aedeagus, are diagnostic characters and provide easy recognition of the new species relative to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Boursin" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[963,1109,151,175]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diagrapha">
<emphasis box="[963,1109,151,175]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">X. diagrapha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in which the thin, elongate sclerotised bar is positioned ventrad and the vesica also recurved ventrad.
</paragraph>
