<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,279]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">
The male genitalia (the presence of the pollex and harpe, the shape of the valvae, the lack of the corona in the cucullus) of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gyulai" authorityYear="2018" box="[290,436,185,209]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Xestia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanceolata">
<emphasis box="[290,436,185,209]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">X. lanceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clearly indicate that it belongs to the subfamily 
<taxonomicName box="[978,1087,186,209]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
<emphasis box="[978,1087,186,209]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">Noctuinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while 
<emphasis box="[1173,1302,186,209]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">B. pygmaea</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1320,1400,186,209]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–10" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1898,1920]" captionTargetBox="[242,1336,336,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,330,1877]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 7–10. Male genitalia. 7. Xestia lanceolata sp. n., holotype, China, Yünnan, slide no. GYP4934 (PGM); 8. Xestia lanceolata sp. n., paratype, China, Yünnan, slide no. GYP4904 (PGM); 9. Xestia diagrapha (Boursin, 1963), China, Sichuan, slide no. GYP2376 (PGM); 10. Brachylomia pygmaea (Draudt, 1950), China, Sichuan, slide no. GYP4905 (PGM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2608057/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) is similar only superficially; the male genitalia (the absence of the pollex, the short sacculus, the presence of a short corona in the cucullus) in this latter species reflect its placement in the subfamily 
<taxonomicName box="[942,1048,255,279]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Xyleninae">
<emphasis box="[942,1048,255,279]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">Xyleninae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
